#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.88"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.88:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.88:0.2"
msgid "9. Channavagga "
msgstr "9. With Channa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.88:0.3"
msgid "88. Puṇṇasutta "
msgstr "88. With Puṇṇa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: Atha → sāvatthinidānaṃ. atha (?)
msgctxt "sn35.88:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā puṇṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And then Venerable Puṇṇa went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.88:1.2"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.88:2.1"
msgid "“Santi kho, puṇṇa, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "“Puṇṇa, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.3"
msgid "Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī. "
msgstr "this gives rise to relishing. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.4"
msgid "‘Nandisamudayā dukkhasamudayo, puṇṇā’ti vadāmi … pe … "
msgstr "Relishing is the origin of suffering, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.88:2.5"
msgid "santi kho, puṇṇa, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe … "
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches … "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.6"
msgid "santi kho, puṇṇa, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.7"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.8"
msgid "Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī. "
msgstr "this gives rise to relishing. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:2.9"
msgid "‘Nandisamudayā dukkhasamudayo, puṇṇā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Relishing is the origin of suffering, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.61, sc3
msgctxt "sn35.88:3.1"
msgid "Santi kho, puṇṇa, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:3.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati, tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato nirujjhati nandī. "
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, relishing ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:3.3"
msgid "‘Nandinirodhā dukkhanirodho, puṇṇā’ti vadāmi … pe … "
msgstr "When relishing ceases, suffering ceases, I say. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.88:3.4"
msgid "santi kho, puṇṇa, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:3.5"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati, tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato nirujjhati nandī. "
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, relishing ceases. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:3.6"
msgid "‘Nandinirodhā dukkhanirodho, puṇṇā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "When relishing ceases, suffering ceases, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.88:4.1"
msgid "Iminā tvaṃ, puṇṇa, mayā saṃkhittena ovādena ovadito katamasmiṃ janapade viharissasī”ti? "
msgstr "Puṇṇa, now that I’ve given you this brief advice, what country will you live in?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.88:4.2"
msgid "“Atthi, bhante, sunāparanto nāma janapado, tatthāhaṃ viharissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, there’s a country called Sunāparanta; I will live there.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.88:5.1"
msgid "“Caṇḍā kho, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā; "
msgstr "“The people of Sunāparanta are wild and rough, Puṇṇa. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:5.2"
msgid "pharusā kho, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.88:5.3"
msgid "Sace taṃ, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā akkosissanti paribhāsissanti, tatra te, puṇṇa, kinti bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "If they abuse and insult you, what will you think of them?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.88:6.1"
msgid "“Sace maṃ, bhante, sunāparantakā manussā akkosissanti paribhāsissanti, tatra me evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "“If they abuse and insult me, I will think: "

#. VAR: me → maṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.88:6.2"
msgid "‘bhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, subhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, yaṃ me nayime pāṇinā pahāraṃ dentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘These people of Sunāparanta are gracious, truly gracious, since they don’t hit me with their fists.’ "

#. VAR: Evamettha → evammettha (?)
msgctxt "sn35.88:6.3"
msgid "Evamettha, bhagavā, bhavissati; "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:6.4"
msgid "evamettha, sugata, bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Holy One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.88:7.1"
msgid "“Sace pana te, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā pāṇinā pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra pana te, puṇṇa, kinti bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But if they do hit you with their fists, what will you think of them then?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.88:8.1"
msgid "“Sace me, bhante, sunāparantakā manussā pāṇinā pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra me evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "“If they hit me with their fists, I’ll think: "

# NOTE: BB’s “give me a blow with a clod” sounds odd, and is overly literal. “Stoning” with leddu is commonly mentioned in both Pali and Sanskrit.
#. VAR: yaṃ me → yaṃ maṃ (s1-3) | evammettha (?)
msgctxt "sn35.88:8.2"
msgid "‘bhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, subhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, yaṃ me nayime leḍḍunā pahāraṃ dentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘These people of Sunāparanta are gracious, truly gracious, since they don’t throw stones at me.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.88:8.3"
msgid "Evamettha, bhagavā, bhavissati; "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:8.4"
msgid "evamettha, sugata, bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Holy One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.88:9.1"
msgid "“Sace pana te, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā leḍḍunā pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra pana te, puṇṇa, kinti bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But if they do throw stones at you, what will you think of them then?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.62, sc10
msgctxt "sn35.88:10.1"
msgid "“Sace me, bhante, sunāparantakā manussā leḍḍunā pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra me evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "“If they throw stones at me, I’ll think: "

msgctxt "sn35.88:10.2"
msgid "‘bhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, subhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, yaṃ me nayime daṇḍena pahāraṃ dentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘These people of Sunāparanta are gracious, truly gracious, since they don’t beat me with a club.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.88:10.3"
msgid "Evamettha, bhagavā, bhavissati; "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:10.4"
msgid "evamettha, sugata, bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Holy One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.88:11.1"
msgid "“Sace pana puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā daṇḍena pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra pana te, puṇṇa, kinti bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But if they do beat you with a club, what will you think of them then?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.88:12.1"
msgid "“Sace me, bhante, sunāparantakā manussā daṇḍena pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra me evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "“If they beat me with a club, I’ll think: "

msgctxt "sn35.88:12.2"
msgid "‘bhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, subhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, yaṃ me nayime satthena pahāraṃ dentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘These people of Sunāparanta are gracious, truly gracious, since they don’t stab me with a knife.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.88:12.3"
msgid "Evamettha, bhagavā, bhavissati; "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:12.4"
msgid "evamettha, sugata, bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Holy One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.88:13.1"
msgid "“Sace pana te, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā satthena pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra pana te, puṇṇa, kinti bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But if they do stab you with a knife, what will you think of them then?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.88:14.1"
msgid "“Sace me, bhante, sunāparantakā manussā satthena pahāraṃ dassanti, tatra me evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "“If they stab me with a knife, I’ll think: "

msgctxt "sn35.88:14.2"
msgid "‘bhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, subhaddakā vatime sunāparantakā manussā, yaṃ maṃ nayime tiṇhena satthena jīvitā voropentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘These people of Sunāparanta are gracious, truly gracious, since they don’t take my life with a sharp knife.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.88:14.3"
msgid "Evamettha, bhagavā, bhavissati; "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:14.4"
msgid "evamettha, sugata, bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Holy One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.88:15.1"
msgid "“Sace pana taṃ, puṇṇa, sunāparantakā manussā tiṇhena satthena jīvitā voropessanti, tatra pana te, puṇṇa, kinti bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But if they do take your life with a sharp knife, what will you think of them then?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.88:16.1"
msgid "“Sace maṃ, bhante, sunāparantakā manussā tiṇhena satthena jīvitā voropessanti, tatra me evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "“If they take my life with a sharp knife, I’ll think: "

msgctxt "sn35.88:16.2"
msgid "‘santi kho tassa bhagavato sāvakā kāyena ca jīvitena ca aṭṭīyamānā harāyamānā jigucchamānā satthahārakaṃ pariyesanti, taṃ me idaṃ apariyiṭṭhaññeva satthahārakaṃ laddhan’ti. "
msgstr "‘There are disciples of the Buddha who looked for someone to assist with slitting their wrists because they were horrified, repelled, and disgusted with the body and with life. And I have found this without looking!’ "

msgctxt "sn35.88:16.3"
msgid "Evamettha, bhagavā, bhavissati; "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:16.4"
msgid "evamettha, sugata, bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I’ll think, Holy One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "sn35.88:17.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, puṇṇa. "
msgstr "“Good, good Puṇṇa! "

msgctxt "sn35.88:17.2"
msgid "Sakkhissasi kho tvaṃ, puṇṇa, iminā damūpasamena samannāgato sunāparantasmiṃ janapade vatthuṃ. "
msgstr "Having such self-control and peacefulness, you will be quite capable of living in Sunāparanta. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:17.3"
msgid "Yassadāni tvaṃ, puṇṇa, kālaṃ maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "Now, Puṇṇa, go at your convenience.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.63, sc18
msgctxt "sn35.88:18.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo bhagavato vacanaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sunāparanto janapado tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "And then Puṇṇa welcomed and agreed with the Buddha’s words. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out for Sunāparanta. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.88:18.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sunāparanto janapado tadavasari. "
msgstr "Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Sunāparanta, "

msgctxt "sn35.88:18.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā puṇṇo sunāparantasmiṃ janapade viharati. "
msgstr "and stayed there. "

#. VAR: paṭivedesi → paṭipādesi (si, pts1) | paṭidesesi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.88:18.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo tenevantaravassena pañcamattāni upāsakasatāni paṭivedesi. "
msgstr "Within that rainy season he confirmed around five hundred male and five hundred female lay followers. And within that same rainy season he realized the three knowledges. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:18.5"
msgid "Tenevantaravassena pañcamattāni upāsikāsatāni paṭivedesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.88:18.6"
msgid "Tenevantaravassena tisso vijjā sacchākāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.88:18.7"
msgid "Tenevantaravassena parinibbāyi. "
msgstr "And within that same rainy season he became completely extinguished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "sn35.88:19.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn35.88:19.2"
msgid "“yo so, bhante, puṇṇo nāma kulaputto bhagavatā saṅkhittena ovādena ovadito, so kālaṅkato. "
msgstr "“Sir, the gentleman named Puṇṇa, who was advised in brief by the Buddha, has passed away. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:19.3"
msgid "Tassa kā gati ko abhisamparāyo”ti? "
msgstr "Where has he been reborn in his next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
#. VAR: kulaputto → kulaputto ahosi (sabbattha)
#. VAR: paccapādi → paccapādī (bj) | saccavādī (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: vihesesi → viheṭhesi (c1)
msgctxt "sn35.88:20.1"
msgid "“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, puṇṇo kulaputto, paccapādi dhammassānudhammaṃ, na ca maṃ dhammādhikaraṇaṃ vihesesi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, Puṇṇa was astute. He practiced in line with the teachings, and did not trouble me about the teachings. "

msgctxt "sn35.88:20.2"
msgid "Parinibbuto, bhikkhave, puṇṇo kulaputto”ti. "
msgstr "Puṇṇa has become completely extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.88:20.3"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

